	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every statistic is a real graduate — maybe you. The thrill of the diploma, and the 2 a.m. worry about whether you chose the right next step. The pressure to land the job, the dorm, the plan, the life everyone keeps asking about. The strange grief of leaving the people and places that made you who you are. The fear that out there, with no GPA to measure by, you might not be enough.</p><p>None of this means something is wrong with you. It means you're stepping into the unknown — and the unknown is honest work for the soul. The good news is that you are not stepping into it alone. There is a Father who has already walked the road ahead of you, and He has something to say about who you are and where you're going.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
