	]}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for graduates`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what almost no one tells you at graduation: the answer to the fear of the unknown isn't a perfect five-year plan, the right offer letter, or finally having it all figured out. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a perfect, holy Father who goes with you into the unknown, because He's already been there.</p><p>You were not made to earn your worth out there. You were made to receive it. And the One who made you doesn't score you by your degree, rank you by your salary, or measure you by your résumé. He calls you His beloved child — not the successful future you, not the impressive you, but <em>you</em>, right now, standing at the edge of the next thing.</p><p>So before you're a graduate, a hire, a major, a job title — you are His. Your heavenly Father wants to be the steady presence underneath every new beginning, the One who says: I go with you, I already know the road, and there is nothing you could achieve that would make Me love you more — or fail at that would make Me love you less.</p>`}
