	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel ready, and the road ahead might still look unclear. That's okay. The Father's love isn't a graduation-day high — it's a foundation, and foundations get built quietly, one day at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father planting something in you that no transition, no rejection, and no unknown can uproot.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I see you standing at the edge of the next thing — the excitement and the fear, the questions about which path and whether you're ready. Hear Me over all of it: I go with you. I've already walked the road ahead, and I will not leave you or forsake you. Be strong and courageous, because you are never stepping into the unknown alone.</p><p>And know this — your worth was never your GPA, your degree, or your résumé. I loved you before you earned a single thing, and I will love you the same whether you succeed or stumble. So come to Me with the fear of the future. I'll guide your steps, I'll strengthen you, and I'll delight in you the whole way. I'm your Father. Wherever you go from here, I'm going too."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for graduates`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for these graduates — for the work they've finished and the unknown they now face. We bless them in this turning point: as they step into the next chapter, let them know deep down that they do not go alone, for You go before them and You go with them, and You already know the road.</p><p>Free them from the fear of the future and the pressure to have it all figured out. Remind them that their worth was never their GPA, their degree, or their résumé — that they are Your beloved before and apart from anything they achieve. Give them wisdom to choose well, courage to begin, and friends who point them back to You. Father, guard them from the lie that success is the measure of their value, and steady them on the late nights when the unknown feels too big.</p><p>Lead them to trust You with all their heart, to lean not on their own understanding, and to let You make their paths straight. Work all things together for their good. And may they wake up every single day knowing they are loved by their heavenly Father, who goes with them wherever they go.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
