	faqs={[
		{ question: `What is a good Bible verse for a graduate?`, answer: `Jeremiah 29:11 (plans for a future and a hope) and Joshua 1:9 (be strong and courageous, your God is with you wherever you go) are the two most popular graduation verses. Proverbs 3:5-6 (trust in the Lord, He'll make your paths straight), Isaiah 41:10 (fear not, I am with you), and Philippians 4:13 (I can do all things through Christ) are also favorites. Read and hear them all free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for graduation cards?`, answer: `For a graduation card, Joshua 1:9, Jeremiah 29:11, Proverbs 3:5-6, and Deuteronomy 31:8 (He goes before you, He will not leave you) all carry a warm "your Father goes with you" blessing that fits a card beautifully. Pair a verse with a short note like "Wherever you go from here, He goes with you." You can read each one free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read to choose the wording you love.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about the future?`, answer: `Scripture says your future is held by a Father who already knows the road. Jeremiah 29:11 says God has plans for your welfare, a future and a hope; Proverbs 3:5-6 promises He'll make your paths straight when you trust Him; and Romans 8:28 says He works all things together for good. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals that God isn't a distant planner but a Father who walks the unknown with you — read those passages free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
