		{ question: `Does my worth depend on my GPA, degree, or career success?`, answer: `No — and that's the heart of this page. Your worth was never your GPA, your degree, or your résumé. Romans 8:28 and Jeremiah 29:11 show a Father invested in you, not your stats, and Philippians 4:13 says your strength comes from Him. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet God as a Father who delights in you before and apart from anything you achieve. Read it free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio for graduates and young adults?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone and read or hear any book — perfect for the dorm, the first apartment, or the commute to a new job as you step into the next chapter.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ a meaningful graduation gift?`, answer: `It's the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so a graduate stepping into the unknown meets the One who goes with them, rather than one more voice telling them to measure up. It's free to read and listen to at fathersheartbible.com/read, which makes it a gift that travels anywhere, costs nothing, and speaks straight to the fear of the future.` },
	]}
